  "prompt": "Where can I get very reasonable price for men's shoes in Sydney?",
  "response": "In Sydney, there are several places where you can find men's shoes at reasonable prices:\n\n1. **Factory Outlet Stores:** These often offer discounted prices on big brands. Check out DFO Homebush or Birkenhead Point Outlet for a variety of options.\n\n2. **Department Stores:** Myer and David Jones often have sales and clearance sections where you can find good deals on men's shoes.\n\n3. **Online Retailers:** Websites like The Iconic, Catch, and Amazon Australia often have competitive prices and frequent sales. They also offer the convenience of shopping from home.\n\n4. **Discount Shoe Stores:** Try places like Payless Shoes or Shoe Warehouse for budget-friendly options.\n\n5. **Unbranded Stores:** Explore local markets and independent shoe stores in suburbs like Newtown or Surry Hills, where unique and affordable options may be available.\n\n6. **Second-Hand Stores:** Shops like Vinnies, Salvos, and other thrift stores can sometimes have gently used shoes at a fraction of the original price.\n\nAlways keep an eye out for seasonal sales, promotional discounts, and sign up for newsletters which might provide additional savings.",
